HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1349
By Littleton
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Stephanie Jan Halaiko
Chivers of Kingston Springs.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of former State Representative Stephanie Jan Halaiko Chivers; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Chivers was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for her fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born in Harrisburg, Pennsylvania, on March 1, 1934, to Stephen and Martha
Halaiko, Stephanie Chivers distinguished herself early as a student athlete, playing tennis at
The Pennsylvania State University before embarking upon a remarkable career in public service
and politics; and
WHEREAS, in 1961, she married her beloved husband, Noel K. Chivers, with whom she
raised two sons, Rusty and Tom; and
WHEREAS, a pioneering figure in Tennessee politics, Mrs. Chivers was the first female
Republican ever elected to the Tennessee House of Representatives from Shelby County; and
WHEREAS, her distinguished career in public service included her tenure in the
administration of President George H.W. Bush in the Office of Presidential Personnel, as well as
her service as an assistant commissioner in the Department of Commerce and Insurance under
Governor Don Sundquist; and
WHEREAS, widely respected for her political acumen and leadership, Stephanie Chivers
served as a longtime senior advisor to United States Senator Lamar Alexander and was elected
by the Tennessee Republican Party State Executive Committee as Republican National
Committeewoman in 2000; and
HJR1349
017561
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Mrs. Chivers's extensive involvement in political campaigns included service
as Tennessee co-chair of Bush-Cheney 2000, work on Bob Corker's United States Senate
campaign, volunteer service for Governor Bill Haslam, and participation in numerous state and
local campaigns; and
WHEREAS, in 2002, she garnered national attention when, in her official capacity, she
granted a boxing license to Mike Tyson for a fight in Memphis; and
WHEREAS, throughout her career, Stephanie Chivers mentored and guided the careers
of countless young women and men in government, politics, business, and community service;
and
WHEREAS, beyond her many professional accomplishments, Mrs. Chivers was an avid
sports fan who especially enjoyed tennis, golf, and football, and she found great pleasure in
reading, bird-watching, and indulging her fondness for sweet treats; and
WHEREAS, her greatest joy was found in the company of her family, friends, and
beloved pets, and she took immense pride in her children and grandchildren, delighting in loving
and spoiling them; and
WHEREAS, Stephanie Chivers departed this life on February 16, 2026, peacefully
surrounded by her loved ones in the comfort of her home in Kingston Springs; and
WHEREAS, in addition to her parents, she was preceded in death by her sisters, Toni,
Marcia, and Patricia, and her daughter-in-law, Lacy; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Chivers is survived by her beloved husband, Noel; her brother, Billy
Halaiko; her sons, Rusty (Lacy) Chivers and Tom (Samantha) Chivers; her grandchildren,
Jessica (Doug) Taggart, Caitlyn (Cody) Anderson, Lila Chivers, Witt Chivers, Max Chivers, and
Avie Chivers; her great-grandchildren, Alexis Taggart, Abram Taggart, Revel Anderson, and
Alden Anderson; and many extended family members and dear friends; and
WHEREAS, a cherished friend, mentor, and leader, Stephanie Chivers touched the lives
of all who knew her with her warmth, generosity, and rare ability to form meaningful and lasting
connections; now, therefore,
- 2 - 017561

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Stephanie Jan Halaiko Chivers, reflecting fondly
upon her impeccable character, her extraordinary life of service, and her enduring legacy of
leadership and compassion.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and extend our
condolences to the family of Mrs. Chivers.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
